item.title: Dwayne Roloson UNBELIEVABLE Saving Sequence vs Tampa Bay (HD Multiview)
item.description:
Dwayne Roloson UNBELIEVABLE Saving Sequence vs Tampa Bay (HD Multiview)
New York -- Dwayne Roloson made an incredible save when he dived back into the net after the puck took a wild bounce off the boards behind him and came out in front. Roloson lunged to block Steve Downie's attempt at a wide-open net and then added another crazy save when he used his left skate to deny Todd Fedoruk's try on the rebound. The puck remained on the line as the Lightning celebrated what they thought was a goal. But play continued, and a lengthy video replay confirmed that the puck didn't cross the line. As you clearly can see in the picture below. http://i295.photobucket.com/albums/mm140/DayWalk3rz/No_Goal.png Keep in mind that the ENTIRE puck has to cross the goal line for it to be a goal.
